reviewText: Nice Yoga practice with some added cardio

There are three separate segments of yoga each about 21-22 minutes and sadsana for five minutes.  The workouts are intermediate and advanced.  I had to learn the accent before having an effective session.  It's rare to find Kriya yoga in a DVD format so I really appreciate this.
this is suppose to be instructional and the yogi is difficult to understand.

It was Ok, dude was odd shaped and not really health looking and I kept thinking as I was trying to enjoy the poses,"I don't want to look like this guy". "is this what I want to look like to be healthy?"

Good authentic stuff.
Wish he would make more.
You rock Ashokananda
It is a little difficult to understand him at times. Some for the poses where a little more complicated. The work out didn't seem to flow as well as other yoga work outs I have done.
